{
  "name": "Crimson Rite",
  "type": "feat",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You must have a token on the scene to use this feature (Warpgate mutation limitation).</p><p>This feature requires the Blood Hunter to have a Hemocraft die scale set on their class with the key set to: crimson-rite</p><p>If you use the D&amp;D Beyond importer this is already done for you.</p><p>This feature will prompt you to select an equipped weapon to apply the bonus damage to.</p><p>This feature will also prompt you to select what Rite to use if you have multiple. Their feature names should be called one of the following:</p><ul><li><p>Crimson Rite: Rite of the Flame</p></li><li><p>Crimson Rite: Rite of the Frozen</p></li><li><p>Crimson Rite: Rite of the Storm</p></li><li><p>Crimson Rite: Rite of the Dead</p></li><li><p>Crimson Rite: Rite of the Oracle</p></li><li><p>Crimson Rite: Rite of the Roar</p></li><li><p>Rite of the Dawn</p></li></ul><p>These match the imported names from the D&amp;D Beyond importer.</p><p><em>This feature is safe to be renamed.</em></p>",
